  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0db8\u0dbb\u0dca\u0daf\u0db1\u0dba \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dda \u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0d91\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d91\u0db4\u0dcf\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Don't send money to this country until there is repression\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Field Marshal Sarath Fonseka, Gampaha District Member of the Samagi Jana Balawega Party, said in Parliament today that he makes a special request to Sri Lankans abroad not to send even one cent to this country as long as the terrorism that suppresses innocent children continues.",
        "He also said that under his government, the security personnel who harass the children involved in the struggle will be severely punished.",
        "Mr. Fonseka said this during the second reading debate on the Budget Appropriation Bill.",
        "The MP said that the country's struggle is not over and it is emerging like a spark under the ashes.",
        "Mr. Sarath Fonseka said that he will give strength to those sparks and said that this country cannot be saved from corruption without struggle.",
        "The MP said that the struggle is not in the body of the people of Pohottuwa, but it is in their stomach as well as in their kitchen and said that someday they too will have to come to the struggle.",
        "Mr. Fonseka also said that he makes a special request to the legal community to come forward to save the children who are being suppressed."
      ],
